quest.name: Like Fine Wine
journal: Teteroon appears to have finished his gift for Buscarron.
Teteroon has finally finished his gift for Buscarron. Deliver the special brand of Qiqirn beverage back to the eponymous proprietor of Buscarron's Druthers in the South Shroud.
Buscarron is delighted to receive the hard liquor brewed by his old friend. However, he is less delighted when he realizes it would be best to age it a year before finally cracking it open.
objectives: Deliver the Qiqirn firewater to Buscarron at Buscarron's Druthers.

dialogue.name: TETEROON
dialogue.text: Teteroon make firewater! Good, good firewater! You take to Buscaroon. Good firewater for good Buscaroon.

dialogue.name: TETEROON
dialogue.text: Tell Buscaroon no drink now. Tell put away one year. One year make best flavor.

dialogue.name: TETEROON
dialogue.text: <sigh> Teteroon hopes Buscaroon happy. Teteroon gives Buscaroon thankies. Many, many thankies. You tell Buscaroon.

dialogue.name: TETEROON
dialogue.text: Teteroon make big shop someday. Biggest shop in Eorzea. Make many, many sparklies. All thanks to good Buscaroon.

dialogue.name: BUSCARRON
dialogue.text:
Ah, you've returned. Thank you for seeing Teteroon's belongings to him.
...What's this? For me?

dialogue.name: BUSCARRON
dialogue.text: Qiqirn firewater! So he remembers my fondness for the drink, does he? Why that old... He... I... Aw, bloody hells! Who's cutting onions back there!?

dialogue.name: BUSCARRON
dialogue.text: He says to shelve it for a year, does he? Aye, that sounds about right. I hate to have to wait, but I reckon it'll be worth it. This stuff has an aroma and body unlike any other drink I know.

dialogue.name: BUSCARRON
dialogue.text: It's going to be a looong year. What say you come back then, friend? We'll see if we can't make it through this bottle together.
